  <div id="tabs-1" style="color:#023c56">IEEE-TSEC Student Activities and Conferences (ISAAC) focuses on inquisitiveness, perseverance and penchant for hard work through fusion of knowledge, experimentation and analysis. It works at encouraging the creativity of the future engineers. Being the annual inter-collegiate technical festival of IEEE-TSEC, ISAAC continues bringing out the best in students through seminars, workshops and contests for over 14 years. ISAAC proudly holds the title of being the largest technical festival under Mumbai University. It is an arena, a platform for young intellectual minds to learn and imbibe technical knowledge, battle in contests honing their creative and technical skills, and win laurels commending their perseverance.<br><br>

ISAAC is a huge endeavor, comprising of top level conferences, technical workshops, contests and exhibitions each year. Each year, the committee strives to exceed expectations, and make ISAAC bigger and better than ever.
<br><br>
ISAAC 2013 was a magnificent enterprise, having a plethora of conferences, seminars, workshops and technical contests. With the number of participants and spectators rising to SEVERAL HUNDREDS, ISAAC 2013 was a resounding success!</div>
	<div id="tabs-2">Every year, ISAAC holds major conferences for the benefit of the students. These conferences are conducted by eminent names in the industrial world, which come to our college to carry out the conference. The conferences revolve around prominent and up-to-date technologies and futuristic ideas, to acquaint students about modern and latest developments in technology. 
<br><br>
ISAAC 2014 conducted Conferences on:
      <br><br>
      1. <b>Software as a service </b>
<br><br>
Conducted by: - Mr. Shrikant Mulik, L & T InfoTech. L & T InfoTech conducted a conference on “Software as a service”. The students learnt how softwares are delivered through internet i.e. instead of installing software how one can access it online. 
<br><br>
      2. <b>Forensics</b> 
<br><br>
Conducted by:- Mr. Sandeepan Mukherjee, Scientific Officer, Department of Virology & Immunology, Haffkine Institute Experts from the Haffkine Institute conducted a conference on the topic “Forensics” where the students learnt the use of forensic science in various fields like criminal, archaeology, pathology, etc. <br><br>
      3. <b>Free and Open Source Software </b>
<br><br>
Conducted by: - Mr. Abhishek Potnis and his team including Mr. Akshat Kedia and Mr. Sushant Hiray, Volunteering at Mozilla India Professionals from Mozilla India conducted a conference on “Free and Open Source Software” where the students acquired detailed knowledge about Open Source Coding and learnt how to create webpages using Mozilla Firefox Browser. 
</div>
  	<div id="tabs-3">ISAAC organizes workshops, divided into the categories of robotics and non-robotics. Several workshops are conducted, where a massive turnout of enthusiastic students learn about computing, web designing, application development, and simple manufacture and programming of bots, among many other workshops. The workshops are highly technical and hence students gain tremendous knowledge about prominent technologies and concepts. <br><br>
      <b>Non-robotics:</b>
  <ul>
    <li>.NET Framework (by Softechs Computer Institute) </li>
    <li>Adobe Photoshop and CorelDraw (by Amplify..The school of passion creativity and growth)</li>
    <li>Linux and CCNA (by St. Angelos Computer Education)</li>
    <li>MATLAB (by Ameya Centre for Robotics and Embedded Systems) </li>
    <li>Cloud Computing (by Mahen Technologies) </li>
    <li>Web Designing (by Infinitech Training Institute) </li>
    <li>Android App Development (by Prisa Technologies) </li>
    <li>Ethical Hacking (by Innobuzz) </li>
    <li>Facebook marketing and search engine optimization (by 3HD Media) </li>
    <li>Java (by CMS Info Systems Pvt. Ltd.) </li>
    <li>Python (by Skynet Secure) </li>
    <li>Deep vein thrombosis (by Yogikripa Medichem Pvt. Ltd.) </li>
    <li>Polymerase chain reaction (by Sciome Training and Research Pvt. Ltd.) </li>
    <li>Photography (by Mr. Manoj Sharma) </li>
    <li>Programming and Data Management with Oracle Databases (by High Technologies Solutions) </li>
    <li>Webmaker HackJam (by Mozilla India)</li>
      </ul>
      <br><br>
      <b>Robotics:</b>
      <ul>
        <li>Accelero-Botics (by Technophilia Systems Pvt. Ltd.)</li>
        <li>iCellBotix (by Technophilia Systems Pvt. Ltd.)</li>
        <li>Robo-Vision (by Technophilia Systems Pvt. Ltd.)</li>
      </ul>
  </div>
  	<div id="tabs-4">Contests are for the tech geeks and aficionados who can’t wait to battle it out in the battlefield. They are high level technical robotic and non-robotic contests, where students learn and compete to win laurels and knowledge. It is truly a battleground for students to test their technical wits and merits against each other. <br><br>
      <b>Non-robotics:</b>
  <ul>
    <li>Codejam</li>
    <li>Occult Coding </li>
    <li>TPP</li>
    <li>Technowiz </li>
    <li>Online Treasure Hunt</li>
    <li>G.A.M.E.R </li>
      </ul>
      <br><br>
      <b>Robotics:</b>
      <ul>
        <li>Throttle</li>
        <li>Wipeout</li>
        <li>RoboSoccer </li>
        <li>Knockout</li>
        <li>Blind Run</li>
      </ul> </div>
  	<div id="tabs-5">IEEE-TSEC comes up with a philanthropic exhibition every year. Started in 2010, exhibiting and appreciating innovation, making the students aware of the technical know-how is our main motto. Through exhibitions we try to showcase the technology to the future generation, giving a wide exposure to technology. Following the tradition set by IEEE-TSEC’s technical team Conatus, the new members of Conatus team exhibited various projects at the exhibition. Following are the list of projects that were exhibited this year:<br><br>
  <ul>
    <li>Automated Cart</li>
    <li>3D Persistence Of Vision</li>
    <li>Bluetooth Home Automation </li>
    <li>Electric Braille Reader </li>
    <li>Isaac Android Application </li>
    <li>Working of a piston engine using Cinema 4D </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
